        <td>Registered acupuncturist / acupuncture</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Intervention</td>
        <td>Acupressure wristband (non-invasive)</td>
        <td>Needle acupuncture (invasive)</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Timing</td>
        <td>Planned peri-operative</td>
        <td>Acute/unscheduled presentations</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Status</td>
        <td>Completed</td>
        <td>In progress</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <p>
    When this research is complete, the case study will walk through all four
    HAIF phases as applied to the emergency department context, including
    adaptations required for acute care settings.
  </p>

